org.sd.bdb
Interface DbIterator<T>

All Superinterfaces:
java.util.Iterator<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseDbIterator, KeyOrderIterator, LongKeyOrderIterator, LongTimeOrderIterator, RawDbIterator, TimeOrderIterator
public interface DbIterator<T>
extends java.util.Iterator<T>

A database iterator differs from a normal iterator in that it must be closed when its use is finished.

try { DbIterator iter = ...; // do stuff } finally { iter.close(); }

Author:
Spence Koehler

LongKeyValuePair seek(long key)
Move the cursor to the given key such that next() will return the next record after the first with the key.

Returns:
the matching key value pair if the key was found and the iterator is positioned at its record such that next() will return the following record; otherwise, return null and leave the position of the cursor unchanged.
